<h2>A better deal for students</h2>
<h4>Being a student means that you have limited time for work, and sometimes your availability changes. Smart But Poor provides you with an easy to manage work availability tool, and puts you in contact with employers and agencies that need your skills, at the times that work for you.
This means that you can set up your schedule in advance and work with one or more employers that can accommodate your flexible schedule.
This also means that you can get more opportunities to work without having to compromise on your study time or social life.</h4>
<br /><h4>Smart But Poor offers you an easy way to list your availability and skills, get in touch with employers, acquire new skills and work experience, and manage a schedule that works best for you.</h4>
<br />
<!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
<br />
<h3>How does it work?</h3>
<br />
<h4><ol> 
<li>You register on our site. Registration is free for students.</li>
<li>You agree to our T&Cs and sign the Contract of Representation.</li>
<li>You accept and sign a Contract of Employment with our local agency.</li>
<li>You select your skills from the available ones.</li>
<li>You set up your available hours for the next 2 weeks.</li>
<li>You check the employers in your area who are looking for people with your skills.</li>
<li>You select the employers you would be interested in working for- in accordance with your preferences of location, culture and pay.</li>
<li>The employer will receive and review your skills.</li>
<li>The employer selects the workers they want to employ.</li>
<li>The employer posts their staffing needs for the upcoming period.</li>
<li>You select the shifts and days you are willing to work.</li>
<li>At the end of the month, you get paid for what you worked.</li>
</ol>
</h4>
